@startuml MarketSense_User_Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #3B7DD8
skinparam ArrowFontColor #555555
skinparam ArrowFontSize 10

skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #3B7DD8
  FontColor #1A1A2E
  FontSize 11
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  DiamondBorderColor #E8A020
  DiamondFontColor #1A1A2E
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #EEF4FF
  BorderColor #3B7DD8
  FontColor #333366
  FontSize 10
}

skinparam swimlane {
  BorderColor #BBCFE8
  TitleBackgroundColor #E3EDF9
  TitleFontSize 12
  TitleFontStyle bold
  TitleFontColor #1A1A2E
}

title <size:17><b>MarketSense - User Flow</b></size>\nAI-Powered Stock Market Companion for Beginner Indian Investors (NSE/BSE)

|User|
|Streamlit Frontend|
|FastAPI Backend|
|AI and ML Engine|
|Data Layer|

' ============================================================
' 1. APP LAUNCH
' ============================================================

|User|
start
:Open MarketSense App;

|Streamlit Frontend|
:Show Engine Initialization Loader\n"Checking database, fetching news, computing signals..."\nRotating Pro Tips display during warmup;

note right
  UX Trust Signal:
  The animated loader is intentional.
  It shows the system is actively
  working for the user.
  Transparency builds trust.
end note

|FastAPI Backend|
:GET /health
Check DB, External APIs, System latency;

|Data Layer|
:Verify data freshness:
- OHLCV prices (max 15 min stale)
- India VIX, USD-INR, Brent Crude
- FII/DII daily flows
- News sentiment scores;

|FastAPI Backend|
if (All systems healthy?) then (YES)
  :Return status: OK;
else (NO - degraded)
  :Return status: DEGRADED
  + identify which source is stale;
  |Streamlit Frontend|
  :Show soft warning banner:
  "Some data may be delayed.
  Results are still shown.";
endif

' ============================================================
' 2. PAGE 1 - MARKET PULSE
' ============================================================

|FastAPI Backend|
:GET /api/v1/market/pulse;

|Data Layer|
:Fetch NIFTY 50 and SENSEX price and pct change
Fetch India VIX level
Fetch FII net buy/sell for today
Fetch DII net buy/sell for today
Fetch sector index pct changes;

|Streamlit Frontend|
:Render Page 1 - Market Pulse
(30-second market overview);

note right
  Market Pulse Display:
  NIFTY 50: 24,320  +0.8%  Mood: Bullish
  India VIX: 13.2 => "Market is calm today"
  FII: +1,240 Cr (Buying)
  DII: -430 Cr (Selling)
  Sector Heatmap: IT +1.4%  Pharma -0.6%

  Every data point has a plain-English label.
  No raw numbers shown without context.
end note

|User|
:Reads 30-second market overview;

if (Wants to explore a sector?) then (YES)
  :Clicks sector tile in heatmap;
  |FastAPI Backend|
  :GET /api/v1/screen with sector filter;
  |Streamlit Frontend|
  :Show sector-filtered stock list with AI signals;
  |User|
  :Browses sector picks;
endif

' ============================================================
' 3. PAGE 2 - TODAY'S PICKS (Core Feature)
' ============================================================

|User|
:Navigate to Page 2 - Today's Picks
(Core Feature / Morning Homepage);

|FastAPI Backend|
:GET /api/v1/stocks/top-picks;

|AI and ML Engine|
:Load pre-computed screener output
Generated nightly at 5:00 PM IST post-close;

note right
  Nightly Screener Pipeline (APScheduler at 5 PM IST):

  Step 1 - Score all NSE 500 stocks:
    - Model confidence (weighted across horizons)
    - Risk-adjusted return (target vs stop loss %)
    - Momentum alignment across timeframes
    - News + FII/DII sentiment score
    - Sector trend alignment

  Step 2 - Apply Beginner Safety Filters:
    EXCLUDE: confidence below 65%
    EXCLUDE: circuit-hit stocks
    EXCLUDE: high VIX correlation (too volatile)
    EXCLUDE: penny stocks under Rs50 or cap under Rs500Cr
    PREFER: Large-cap and Mid-cap (NIFTY 500)

  Step 3 - Sector Diversification:
    Maximum 2 picks per sector

  Step 4 - Store Top 5 Picks in DB with full metadata:
    direction, confidence, entry zone,
    target, stop loss, plain-English reason,
    bear case, horizon tag
end note

|Streamlit Frontend|
:Render 5 Stock Cards;

note right
  Each Stock Card shows:
  ------------------------------------------
  RELIANCE INDUSTRIES   Sector: Energy
  ------------------------------------------
  BUY   Confidence: 78%  [||||||||..]
  ------------------------------------------
  Entry: Rs2,840 - Rs2,860
  Target: Rs2,990   Stop Loss: Rs2,780
  ------------------------------------------
  Why?
   "More buyers than sellers right now"
   "Low downside vs upside potential"
  ------------------------------------------
  Horizon: Short-term (1-5 days)
  [View Deep Dive]
end note

|User|
:Reviews 5 curated picks
No chart-reading required;

' ============================================================
' 4. PAGE 3 - STOCK DEEP DIVE
' ============================================================

if (Clicks a stock card?) then (YES)

  |User|
  :Click card to open Page 3 - Stock Deep Dive;

  |FastAPI Backend|
  :GET /api/v1/stocks/SYMBOL/predict
  GET /api/v1/stocks/SYMBOL/news
  GET /api/v1/stocks/SYMBOL/history
  GET /api/v1/stocks/SYMBOL/profile;

  |AI and ML Engine|
  :Load predictions for all horizons:
  - Short-term  =>  XGBoost model
  - Swing       =>  Random Forest model
  - Long-term   =>  Prophet model
  - Intraday    =>  LSTM (if data feed available);

  :Generate plain-English explanation
  from top 3 model key drivers;

  |Streamlit Frontend|
  :Render Deep Dive Page;

  note right
    Deep Dive Layout:
    [Tabs] Intraday | Short | Swing | Long-term
    --------------------------------------------------
    Interactive price chart with prediction overlay
    --------------------------------------------------
    News Sentiment Timeline (last 7 days)
      Positive / Neutral / Negative per day
    --------------------------------------------------
    "Explain It To Me" Section:
      "Strong momentum - more buyers than sellers"
      "Safe margins - risk/reward is favorable"
      "Macro-Headwinds - crude oil rising, caution"
    --------------------------------------------------
    Bear Case (always alongside bull case):
      "Global sell-off could reverse this trend"
    --------------------------------------------------
    Historical accuracy for this stock:
      "Last 10 Short-term calls: 7 correct (70%)"
    --------------------------------------------------
    Tooltips on every technical term.
    Entry + Target + Stop Loss always shown together.
  end note

  |User|
  :Reads plain-English explanation and risk levels;

  if (Wants a different horizon?) then (YES)
    |User|
    :Clicks Swing or Long-term tab;
    |Streamlit Frontend|
    :Reload prediction for selected horizon;
    |User|
    :Reviews new Entry, Target, Stop Loss;
  endif

  if (Wants to add to watchlist?) then (YES)
    |User|
    :Clicks Add to Watchlist;
    |FastAPI Backend|
    :POST /api/v1/watchlist
    body: symbol and horizon;
    |Data Layer|
    :Persist symbol to watchlist table;
    |Streamlit Frontend|
    :Show confirmation: "Added to Watchlist";
  endif

endif

' ============================================================
' 5. PAGE 4 - MY WATCHLIST
' ============================================================

if (User opens Watchlist?) then (YES)

  |User|
  :Open Page 4 - My Watchlist;

  |FastAPI Backend|
  :GET /api/v1/watchlist
  Returns all stocks with latest predictions;

  |Data Layer|
  :Fetch most recent prediction
  for each watchlisted symbol;

  |Streamlit Frontend|
  :Render watchlist rows:
  - Signal: BUY / HOLD / AVOID
  - Confidence bar
  - Entry / Target / Stop Loss
  - Alert badge if confidence shifted 10%+;

  |User|
  :Scans watchlist for updated signals and alerts;

  if (Alert badge visible?) then (YES)
    |User|
    :Clicks alert to read updated signal
    and reason for the change;
  endif

  if (Wants to remove a stock?) then (YES)
    |User|
    :Clicks remove icon;
    |FastAPI Backend|
    :DELETE /api/v1/watchlist/SYMBOL;
    |Data Layer|
    :Remove symbol from watchlist table;
    |Streamlit Frontend|
    :Stock removed from list;
  endif

endif

' ============================================================
' 6. PAGE 5 - MODEL ACCURACY TRACKER
' ============================================================

if (User opens Accuracy Tracker?) then (YES)

  |User|
  :Open Page 5 - Model Accuracy Tracker;

  |FastAPI Backend|
  :GET /api/v1/accuracy;

  |AI and ML Engine|
  :Load from Prediction Archive DB:
  - Overall directional accuracy %
  - Win rate at 65%, 70%, 80% confidence bands
  - Per-sector accuracy breakdown
  - Per-horizon accuracy: Short, Swing, Long
  - Accuracy trend over last 30 days;

  |Streamlit Frontend|
  :Render Accuracy Dashboard:
  - "7 of last 10 Short-term picks were correct"
  - Prediction vs Actual chart
  - Breakdown by horizon and sector
  - Model track record over time;

  note right
    Trust-Building Feature:
    Full transparency on wins AND losses.
    Users see the honest track record
    before making any investment decision.
    Champion vs Challenger model comparison
    shown after each weekly Sunday retrain.
  end note

  |User|
  :Reviews model track record;

endif

' ============================================================
' 7. BACKGROUND AUTOMATION NOTE
' ============================================================

|AI and ML Engine|
:Background Automation (always running, zero user action needed);

note right
  APScheduler Jobs:

  Every 15 min (market hours 9:15 AM to 3:30 PM IST):
    Price fetcher (yfinance/NSE API)
    => Feature recomputation
    => Prediction refresh for watchlisted stocks

  Every 30 min:
    News RSS ingestion
    => FinBERT/VADER sentiment scoring
    => Live signal update

  Daily at 7:00 AM IST (pre-market):
    USD/INR, Brent Crude, India VIX,
    10Y G-Sec yield, FII/DII flows

  Daily at 5:00 PM IST (post-close):
    Full NSE 500 screener run
    => Composite scoring => Beginner filter
    => Sector diversification
    => Store Top 5 Picks to DB
    => Archive yesterday's predictions vs actuals

  Weekly (Sunday midnight):
    Retrain all 4 models on fresh data
    => Champion/Challenger comparison
    => Deploy new model only if accuracy improves

  Every hour:
    Stale data alert if any source goes silent
    Auto-skip jobs on NSE holidays
end note

' ============================================================
' 8. FINAL USER DECISION
' ============================================================

|User|
:User now has:
- BUY / HOLD / AVOID signal
- Entry price, Target, Stop Loss in Rs
- Plain-English reasoning with no jargon
- Bear case and risk level understood
- Confidence % with historical context;

if (Ready to act on a signal?) then (INVEST)
  :Takes informed investment decision
  via their own broker app;
  note right
    MarketSense = Guidance only.
    No real-money trading integration.
    No financial advice, prediction only.
    Stop Loss always given with every call.
  end note
else (WAIT or MONITOR)
  :Monitors watchlist for
  confidence change or better signal;
endif

:Returns next morning for fresh Top 5 Picks
The cycle repeats automatically every day;

stop

@enduml
